[h1]The Crimson Bath[/h1]

An ancient rite. A captive's blood, an iron table, the years given back by morning.

[h2]What it does[/h2]
A player decision for an aged ruler with young captives. Each old-age malady undone (infirm, clouded eyes, faltering heart, fragile bones, withering mind) costs one captive under thirty. The rite plays out one captive per screen.

[h2]Consequences[/h2]
[list]
[*] Branded a witch.
[*] Each sacrificed captive's close family carries -50 opinion for fifteen years, stacking.
[*] A whispered nickname if you have none: the Vampire, the Strigoi, the Pale, the Red, or the Undying.
[*] Sadistic rulers see extra flavor at each kill; callous or sadistic rulers recover small stress per captive.
[*] Faiths without ritual sacrifice: 10% chance per captive to come out of the rite callous, with stress relief.
[/list]

[h2]Compatibility[/h2]
CK3 1.19. Five-year cooldown. Does not edit vanilla files. Player only; the AI will not use it.
